    {
      "text": "# Phase 42: Entity Subject Field\n\n## Status: COMPLETED\n\nAdd a human-readable `subject` (mnemonic name) to Requests, Plans, and Reviews so users can quickly identify what each entity is about in lists, detail views, and cross-references.\n\n## Executive Summary\n\n**Problem:**\nWhen listing requests, plans, or reviews, the only identifying information is a trace ID (UUID). Users must read the full body or open the detail view to understand what a given entity is about. This makes the TUI tables, CLI lists, and linked navigation difficult to scan.\n\n**Solution:**\nIntroduce a `subject` string field across all three entity types:\n\n1. **Requests**: Set via `--subject \"...\"` CLI option, or generated by the agent when processing the request, with a text-extraction fallback.\n\n1.",
