    {
      "text": "- The agent prompt includes an instruction: *\"Provide a `subject` field: a concise one-line summary (≤ 80 chars) describing the request's goal, suitable for display in lists and tables.\"*\n- The `subject` field is added to the plan response schema / structured output format.\n- On receiving the agent's response, the system **validates** the subject:\n  - Non-empty string\n  - Single line (no `\\n`)\n  - Length ≤ 80 characters\n  - Not a repetition of the trace ID or generic filler (e.g., not just \"Request\")\n- If validation passes → use the agent's subject.\n- If validation fails → fall through to Tier 2.\n\n#### Tier 2: Text-Extraction Fallback\n\nUsed when: (a) `--subject` is not provided, (b) agent omits subject, or (c) agent returns invalid subject.",
