    {
      "text": "1. Take the `description` argument (inline) or the first non-empty line of the file (with `--file`).\n\n1.\n1.\n1.\n\n```typescript\nexport function extractFallbackSubject(text: string, maxLength = 60): string {\nconst firstLine = text.split(\"\\n\").find((l) => l.trim().length > 0) |  | \"\";\n  const cleaned = firstLine.replace(/^[\\s#\\-*>\\d.]+/, \"\").trim();\n  if (cleaned.length <= maxLength) return cleaned;\n  const truncated = cleaned.substring(0, maxLength).replace(/\\s+\\S*$/, \"\");\n  return truncated + \"…\";\n}\n```text\n\n#### Resolution Order\n\n```text\n\n1. --subject \"...\" provided by user  →  use as-is (validate length)\n\n1.\n```text\n\n### 3. Subject Propagation Chain",
